HEADWORD: Cespitose
<hw>Ces"pi*tose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>caespes</ets> turf.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the form a
piece of turf, <it>i. e.</it>, many stems from one rootstock or from
many entangled rootstocks or roots.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>c⟦ae⟧spitose</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cespitous</ent>⟦br⟧
